{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-8e843801b01ac00d", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# Audio-DeepThinker: Progressive Reasoning-Aware Reinforcement Learning for High-Quality Chain-of-Thought Emergence in Audio Language Models\narXiv: 2604.18187\nAuthors: Xiang He, Chenxing Li, Jinting Wang, Yan Rong, Tianxin Xie, Wenfu Wang, Li Liu, Dong Yu\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: audio_understanding\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose a hybrid reasoning similarity reward that directly supervises the quality of generated reasoning chains by combining LLM-based logical evaluation with embedding-based semantic alignment, jointly addressing the dual challenges of reasoning soundness and audio grounding.\n  2. We demonstrate that high-quality CoT reasoning can emerge through pure RL exploration from an instruction-tuned LALM without prior chain-of-thought capability, enabled by a progressive two-stage curriculum that establishes foundational patterns and then refines them on challenging boundary cases.\n  3. Audio-DeepThinker achieves state-of-the-art results on MMAR, MMAU-test-mini, and MMSU, winning 1st Place in the Single Model Track of the Interspeech 2026 Audio Reasoning Challenge.\n  4. Mechanistic interpretability analyses reveal that RL training primarily reshapes upper-layer MoE gating mechanisms and that reasoning tokens crystallize progressively in the upper transformer layers, providing novel insights into how audio reasoning capabilities are acquired through exploration.\n\nTags: LALM, LALM/理解型, LALM/后训练-GRPO", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "29c5a6fb-eb9f-417d-82a5-6fe6a24f3989", "uuid": "451d8a41-5899-4a7e-90be-0827a4bcf5c8", "timestamp": "2026-07-24T07:43:39.701Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# Audio-DeepThinker: Progressive Reasoning-Aware Reinforcement Learning for High-Quality Chain-of-Thought Emergence in Audio Language Models\narXiv: 2604.18187\nAuthors: Xiang He, Chenxing Li, Jinting Wang, Yan Rong, Tianxin Xie, Wenfu Wang, Li Liu, Dong Yu\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: audio_understanding\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose a hybrid reasoning similarity reward that directly supervises the quality of generated reasoning chains by combining LLM-based logical evaluation with embedding-based semantic alignment, jointly addressing the dual challenges of reasoning soundness and audio grounding.\n  2. We demonstrate that high-quality CoT reasoning can emerge through pure RL exploration from an instruction-tuned LALM without prior chain-of-thought capability, enabled by a progressive two-stage curriculum that establishes foundational patterns and then refines them on challenging boundary cases.\n  3. Audio-DeepThinker achieves state-of-the-art results on MMAR, MMAU-test-mini, and MMSU, winning 1st Place in the Single Model Track of the Interspeech 2026 Audio Reasoning Challenge.\n  4. Mechanistic interpretability analyses reveal that RL training primarily reshapes upper-layer MoE gating mechanisms and that reasoning tokens crystallize progressively in the upper transformer layers, providing novel insights into how audio reasoning capabilities are acquired through exploration.\n\nTags: LALM, LALM/理解型, LALM/后训练-GRPO", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-b56663bf66ad6a0d", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# EvA: An Evidence-First Audio Understanding Paradigm for LALMs\narXiv: 2603.27667\nAuthors: Xinyuan Xie, Shunian Chen, Zhiheng Liu, Yuhao Zhang, Zhiqiang Lv, Liyin Liang, Benyou Wang\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: audio_understanding\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Identification and empirical validation of the \"evidence bottleneck\" in Large Audio Language Models, demonstrating that upstream perception is a greater limitation than downstream reasoning.\n  2. Proposal of EvA, a dual-path architecture that preserves acoustic evidence before reasoning through hierarchical aggregation and non-compressive, time-aligned fusion.\n  3. Release of EvA-Perception, a large-scale open-source training dataset for evidence-aware audio understanding, alongside the EvA model which achieves the best open-source Perception results on MMAU, MMAR, and MMSU.\n\nTags: LALM, LALM/理解型", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "29c5a6fb-eb9f-417d-82a5-6fe6a24f3989", "uuid": "2005be94-73c9-4d52-b6eb-8da5eeb8674f", "timestamp": "2026-07-24T07:43:39.945Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# EvA: An Evidence-First Audio Understanding Paradigm for LALMs\narXiv: 2603.27667\nAuthors: Xinyuan Xie, Shunian Chen, Zhiheng Liu, Yuhao Zhang, Zhiqiang Lv, Liyin Liang, Benyou Wang\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: audio_understanding\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Identification and empirical validation of the \"evidence bottleneck\" in Large Audio Language Models, demonstrating that upstream perception is a greater limitation than downstream reasoning.\n  2. Proposal of EvA, a dual-path architecture that preserves acoustic evidence before reasoning through hierarchical aggregation and non-compressive, time-aligned fusion.\n  3. Release of EvA-Perception, a large-scale open-source training dataset for evidence-aware audio understanding, alongside the EvA model which achieves the best open-source Perception results on MMAU, MMAR, and MMSU.\n\nTags: LALM, LALM/理解型", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
